#import "template.typ": *

#let metadata = (
  title: "Area Solo Consolidation",
  unit: "Group A (3-Axis) | Phase 4 — Lesson 7 | E9, E10, E14, E15, E16",
  author: "C.Moroney",
)

#let lesson = (
title: [Area Solo Consolidation]

,aim: [
Build solo training area experience, consolidate all Phase 4 manoeuvre elements toward C standard, and maintain full independence in pre-flight administration.
]

,overview: [
Lesson 4.7 is the area solo consolidation phase, structured in a similar way to Phase 2 Stage C5. Multiple supervised solo training area flights are conducted, with the instructor performing periodic dual check flights to assess progress toward C standard. The student handles all pre-flight administration independently. The instructor spot-checks rather than leads. This stage continues until the student has accumulated sufficient solo training area experience for the instructor to be confident that all Phase 4 elements are approaching or at C standard, and the student is ready for Phase 5 flight test preparation.
]

,learning_outcomes: [
#text(size:12pt)[*Knowledge*]
- Describe the flight test standards for all Phase 4 elements (E9, E10, E14, E15, E16)
- Explain the self-brief requirements for a training area solo flight
- Identify the minimum experience requirements before the Phase 5 flight test preparation commences
- Describe the considerations for operating at an alternate aerodrome: ERSA entry review; unfamiliar aerodrome circuit procedures; CTAF frequency and call sequence; runway surface and length assessment

#text(size:12pt)[*Skills*]
- Conduct solo training area flights, managing all elements without instructor input
- Apply HASSELL before stalling or steep turns
- Manage all pre-flight administration independently: NAIPS TAF/GAF/GPWT, NOTAMs, maintenance release review and brief
- Fly Phase 4 manoeuvres to progressively tighter tolerances approaching C standard on dual check flights

#text(size:12pt)[*Non-Technical Skills*]
- [SA] Full PIC situational awareness with no instructor on board; continuous airspace and traffic awareness
- [TEM] Identify and manage all training area threats without prompting; apply HASSELL discipline solo
- [HF] Build confidence and automaticity in training area operations; recognise and manage personal fatigue; know when to terminate a session
- [CRM] Self-brief before every solo departure; self-debrief after each session; record deviations honestly
]

,theory_knowledge: [
- Consolidation of all Phase 4 reading
- Theory exams: BAK, Air Legislation, Human Factors must be complete before Phase 5 commences
]

,ground_brief_topics: [
Total time: 15 minutes (solo days) / 25 minutes (dual check days) \
Equipment required: Student training record, VNC, ERC-L \

*Pre-Solo Self-Brief Template* (every solo session)
- NAIPS: TAF, GAF, and GPWT obtained and interpreted; conditions suitable for planned flight duration?
- BOM radar: precipitation checked as supplemental
- NOTAMs: checked; any restricted areas active? Any traffic?
- Maintenance release: reviewed; all items acceptable; anything to brief instructor?
- EFATO plan
- Radio failure plan: what will I do if radio fails in the training area?
- HASSELL if required for stalling or steep turns
- Training area boundaries: noted
- Personal fitness: IMSAFE complete; am I fit to fly today?

*C Standard Target Review* (dual check days only — 10 minutes)
- Review current standard for each Phase 4 element against C standard criteria
- Identify 1–2 items closest to C standard and 1–2 items still at S standard; plan the dual check to target these
- C standard: consistent, professional execution with no instructor input or correction
]

,ground_tasks:[
#text(size:12pt)[*Instructor*]
- Spot-check student's NAIPS weather interpretation: TAF, GAF, and GPWT read correctly? Conditions suitable?
- Spot-check NOTAM brief: anything relevant missed?
- Spot-check maintenance release review: all key items covered?
- Confirm area solo weather minima are met before student departs
- Observe solo flights; confirm student departs and returns safely; radio available

#text(size:12pt)[*Student*]
- Access NAIPS independently; obtain TAF, GAF, and GPWT; check BOM radar; brief instructor
- Check NOTAMs independently; brief instructor on any relevant items
- Review maintenance release independently; brief instructor on all items checked and anything found
- Complete IMSAFE self-assessment and operations whiteboard
- Deliver pre-solo brief to instructor including all items from the self-brief template above
- Lead pre-flight inspection; complete all documentation independently
]

,in_flight_tasks:[
#text(size:12pt)[*Solo Training Area Flights*]
- Student conducts solo training area flights; instructor observes progress from the aerodrome
- Instructor contacts student by radio only if a safety concern is observed
- Student applies HASSELL where required — non-negotiable solo
- Student manages all area operations, airspace awareness, and radio calls independently

#text(size:12pt)[*Dual Check flights — conducted at instructor's discretion*]
- Instructor assesses C standard progress against each Phase 4 competency variable
- Assessed elements: E9 (steep turns, spiral dive, slipping turn), E10 (scenario stalls), E14 (FLWOP, precautionary search), E15 (airspace management, dead reckoning), E16 (unusual attitudes, emergency actions)
- Identify progress trajectory; set specific C standard targets for remaining solo sessions
]

,common_errors:[
Element-specific errors: refer to common errors in each preceding Phase 4 lesson plan for remediation guidance.
]

,post_flight:[
- *After solo sessions*: Student self-debriefs to instructor; describes each manoeuvre; identifies deviations and causes; confirms HASSELL was applied; confirms airspace was managed
- *After dual check flights*: Instructor provides assessment against C standard; identifies specific targets for remaining solo sessions
- *Pre-flight admin spot-check*: Instructor provides feedback on GAF interpretation, NOTAM brief, and maintenance release review quality
- *Progress tracking*: Record solo hours and dual check results; assess trajectory toward Phase 5 readiness
]

,standards_for_progression:[
*Minimum requirements before advancing to Phase 5:*
- ☐ Sufficient solo training area experience for instructor to be confident all Phase 4 elements are at or approaching C standard
- ☐ All Phase 4 elements at or approaching C standard on dual check
- ☐ BAK exam passed *(minimum 80%, KDR required)*
- ☐ Air Legislation exam passed *(minimum 80%, KDR required)*
- ☐ Human Factors exam passed *(minimum 80%, KDR required, or approved course)*
- ☐ Total flight hours reviewed; on track for 20 hours total (5 hours PIC) before flight test

#text(size:12pt)[*Solo Standard (S) — minimum for area solo operations*]
- HASSELL completed before required sequence and every 15 minutes without omission
- All manoeuvres managed safely without instructor input
- Airspace managed continuously; no boundary proximity events
- Pre-flight admin completed independently

#text(size:12pt)[*Certificate Standard (C) — target before Phase 5*]
- *E9*: 60° steep turns ±5° AoB, ±100 ft, rollout ±10°; spiral dive recovery correct
- *E10*: All scenario stalls managed at or before onset; height loss ≤300 ft; HASSELL every 15 min
- *E14*: Best glide within 5 seconds; FLWOP to 1000/500 ft; MAYDAY simulated; precautionary search correct
- *E15*: Airspace continuously managed; circuit join correct
- *E16*: Both unusual attitude recoveries correct; emergency actions from memory
- *Pre-flight admin*: Fully independent; GAF interpreted correctly; NOTAMs thorough; maintenance release reviewed completely
- *Alternate aerodrome*: Can describe the planning considerations for an unplanned diversion to an unfamiliar aerodrome; correctly interprets ERSA entry for a nominated alternate

- *Outcome*: Solo hours recorded in logbook and training record. Dual check results recorded per element. Phase 5 commences when minimum requirements are met.
]

,safety:[
- *Weather*: Area solo minima apply: ceiling >2500 ft AGL; visibility >8 km; no significant weather turbulence or convective activity in training area; crosswind within solo authorisation limit
- *Maintenance release*: Student must review and brief instructor before every solo flight; any concern = consult instructor before flying
- *HASSELL*: Student confirms HASSELL plan before every solo departure; brief recovery heights before flight
- *TEM*:
  - Instructor confirms area solo weather minima are met before every solo departure
  - If student reports any concern after a solo session — debrief thoroughly before the next flight
  - If fatigue is detected during self-debrief — end the session; do not continue solo flying
  - Maintenance release review is the student's responsibility — safety-critical habit that must be established before the flight test
]

,homework:[
- Complete any outstanding theory exams before Phase 5
- Before every solo session, complete the pre-solo self-brief before arriving at the aerodrome:
  - NAIPS weather; EFATO plan; HASSELL heights; airspace boundaries; personal fitness
- Reflect after every solo session:
  - "Which Phase 4 element is furthest from C standard? What specific aspect needs the most work?"
]
)

#show: body => lesson_plan(metadata, lesson, body)